cs.NA, cs.AI, cs.SI, cs.DS, cs.LG 

The paper proposes a framework for surrogate modeling and global sensitivity analysis, which involves numerical methods and algorithms for optimization and data analysis. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.NA (Numerical Analysis), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). The paper also deals with data analysis and machine learning techniques, which are relevant to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.LG (Machine Learning).
